  content: "I would not describe Tool as a “band” or a “group”, Tool is an experience and for those who have not had the pleasure of hearing such a unique sound, I will try my best to elaborate why I’ve selected them. The band is backed by the LEGENDARY drummer, Danny Carey - iconically known for his unorthodox style of playing. His ability to express emotion and feeling each snap of the stick sends an exhilarating feeling down your spine. Pneuma is Danny’s “magnum opus” - it is a masterpiece, the song begins with a three minute intro which straps you in for the ride, before evolving into a mesh of polyrhythms, tempo changes, and layered instrumentation that feels ambiguous and unpredictable. This unorthodox style is what connects the song to my discourse community within PLT/compiler design. Compilers are full of depth, that is to say - there are many “paths” one could take with respect to being a compiler engineer.  One could spend years studying how to build parsers, improve lexical analysis, while another focuses on optimization and formal verification without ever seeing each other's sides. The balance between unpredictability and rigor is what makes both Pneuma and PLT so captivating to me.",
